defaultSave the Children is the world’s independent children’s rights organisation, working in more than 120 countries. We save children's lives. We fight for their rights. We help them fulfil their potential.
defaultWe have been operating in Burma since 1995
default, and we 
defaultwork 
defaulton the ground 
defaultwith DFID. Our work there spans multiple sectors, including education, protection, child rights governance, health, nutrition and humanitarian response. 
defaultIn 2012, we
default reached 3.9m beneficiaries through programmes worth £22m. 
defaultWe currently deploy 
defaultstaff in 31 sub-offices spanning six regions and four states. 
defaultSave the Children
default can offer field-based evidence from our research, programme ex
defaultperience and local partners to inform the IDC’s inquiry.
defaultWe have focused our submission on the following four issues:
